{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 15:02:20.786513", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"web_server_1\", \"server_access_router\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"mac_address_conflict\"]\n\nRecommended next steps (optional, not submitted):\n- On web_server_1: verify and, if unintended, change the interface MAC to a unique value (ip link set dev eth0 address <new-mac>) or remove any static MAC assignment from its configuration/VM template.\n- On server_access_router: inspect br0 and member interfaces for static MAC configuration or bridge MAC inheritance; set a unique bridge MAC if needed.\n- Inspect switch CAM/MAC tables and packet captures on the server access ports to confirm which device is advertising the MAC more frequently.\n- After fixing MACs, clear ARP caches (ip neigh flush) on affected hosts and verify stability with repeated pings and ARP table checks.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2193, "output_tokens": 186, "total_tokens": 2379, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
